# This ENV file uses defaults based on my needs for US+WORLD 1G1R with Exclusions for Non Retail, Unlicensed games
# and Switch/Virtual Console titles that were never sold in stores for the original hardware.
# Configure everything to suit your own needs, I have left these settings in simply as an example



# DAT File - **This MUST be set or IGIR Shell Tools will Exit**
# Full or relative path from the IGIRST.SH file as well as wildcards in the DAT filename work. If using a wildcard, ensure only 1 DAT exists for the system.
dat="./dats/nintendo/Nintendo - Game Boy Advance (Parent-Clone)*.*"

# Input ROMs Directory - **This MUST be set or IGIR Shell Tools will Exit**
# Full or relative path from the IGIRST.SH file will work here.
input="../Nintendo/Game Boy Advance/Roms"

# Output ROMs Directory - **This MUST be set or IGIR Shell Tools will Exit**
# Full or relative path from the IGIRST.SH file will work here, as does using the input variable for the same directory.
output=$input

# Backup for cleanup - **This MUST be set or IGIR Shell Tools will Exit**
# You don't have to keep backups and can select otherwise, but a check is done for this or IGIR will error if selecting a command with backups.
# The directory doesn't have to exist, and will not be created if not using a command with backups.
backup="$output/../backup"

# Regions - At least one region must be specified here, in order of preference
regions="USA,WORLD"

# Excludes in Glob format - Can be empty
exclude="(2 Game Pack|2 Games in 1|2 Great Games|2 in 1 Game Pack|2-in-1 Fun Pack|4 Games on One Game Pak|Barbie Superpack|Castlevania Double Pack|Combo Pack|Crash & Spyro Superpack|Crash Superpack|Dora the Explorer Double Pack|e-Reader|Evercade|GBA Jukebox|Limited Run Games|Mega Man Battle Network Legacy Collection|Sportsmans Pack 2 in 1|Spyro Superpack|\(Switch|Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles Double Pack|Virtual Console|Yu-Gi-Oh\! Double Pack)"

# ROM Options - Can be empty, set whatever IGIR options you want to use here
options="--single --no-bios --only-retail --no-unlicensed --prefer-revision newer"

#Report Filename - **This MUST be set or IGIR Shellt Tools will Exit**
# Full or relative path from the IGIRST.SH file will work here, as does using the output variable for the same directory.
report="$output/../Nintendo - Game Boy Advance (Parent-Clone).csv"
